                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/29868: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-24T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 24, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. We found your 805, June 21, of interest but wish to avoid any action at this
                    time which would have effect of again projecting us into the “Finnish problem.”
                    Hence you should not call on Ryti as suggested in paragraph numbered 4 of your
                    telegram. However, as we continue to feel that your note of April 8 referred to
                    is in full effect you may in your conversations make appropriate reference
                    thereto.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
